Total snow accumulations between 10 and 25 inches possible. Washington Pass will see more than 18 inches. Winds could gust as high as 45 mph. * WHERE...Washington Pass.
entry.cap:areaDesc: Western Chelan County; Western Okanogan County

entry.title: Flood Watch issued November 09 at 10:52AM PST by NWS
entry.summary: ...FLOOD WATCH IN EFFECT FROM FRIDAY EVENING THROUGH SUNDAY MORNING... * WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is possible. * WHERE...A portion of northwest Washington, including the following county, Mason. * WHEN...From Friday evening through Sunday morning.
entry.cap:areaDesc: Mason

entry.title: Fire Weather Watch issued November 09 at 1:16PM MST until November 10 at 5:00PM MST by NWS
entry.summary: ...FIRE WEATHER WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM FRIDAY MORNING THROUGH FRIDAY AFTERNOON FOR GUSTY WEST WINDS AND LOW HUMIDITY... * AFFECTED AREA...Fire weather zones 428 and 429. * WIND...West winds of 15 to 20 mph sustained with gusts around 25 mph. * HUMIDITY...Afternoon humidity 10 to 15 percent.
entry.cap:areaDesc: Southern Laramie Range; Southern Laramie Valley
